02 June - Bread (easiest loaf you'll ever make)

1 tablespoon sugar
1 tablespoon (1 packet) yeast
1 tablespoon salt
2 cups warm water
5-6 cups flour
corn meal
boiling water

Add sugar and yeast to warm water and let dissolve. Gradually add salt and flour to liquid and mix thoroughly until dough pulls from sides of bowl. Turn out onto floured surface to knead. Fold far edge of dough back over on iteself toward you. Press dough away with heels of hands. After each push, rotate dough 90 degrees. Repeat process in a rhythmic, rocking motion for about 3 minutes. Let dough rest while you scrape out and grease mixing bowl. Knead dough again about 3 more minutes until bouncy and smooth. Place dough in bowl and turn over once to grease the top. Cover with damp towl or plastic wrap and let rise until doubled in bulk (1-2 hours). Punch down dough with fist and briefly knead out gas bubbles. Cut in half and shape into 2 italian or french style loaves. Place on cookie sheet generously sprinkled with corn meal. Let dough rest 10 minutes. 

Quick method
Lightly slaksh the tops 3 or more times diagonally and brush with cold water. Place on racks in cold oven. Bake at 400F for 35 to 40 minutes until crust is golden brown and sounds hollow to the touch. 

Traditional Method:
Let loaves rise 45 minutes. Preheat oven to 450F for 15 minutes. Pour 2-3 cups of boiling water into a roasting pan. Carefully place on oven bottom. Place bread on rack above pan and bake 20 minutes. Turn oven off and allow bread to remain for 5 more minutes. 